Vheadline
p2
VInnovation and perfect execution
p3
sVnews
p4
VKalabharati last Saturday witnessed a novel effort ensemble of women artistes  Ranjani Venkatesh on mridangam and Bhagyalakshmi M. Krishna on morsing,  J. Yogavandana on veena and Deepa K. Murty on violin, with Sukkanya Ramagopal in the lead with six ghatams rendered the concert titled Sthree Thaal Tarang  Layaraaga Sangamama. The items they performed includedSri Mahaganapathim(Gowla), a compositionKuntalavarali, brief elaboration ofBantureethikoluvu(Hamsanaadam),Terateegayaraada(Goulipanthu), ragam tanam and pallavi in Gambheeranata with swaram in Raagamalika coupled with structured exercises with gathi (Chaturasram, Trisram and Khandam) and yathi variations.The thani led by Sukkanya on the ghatam with resplendent responses on morsing, Konnakkol (oral rendering of the bholes) by Sukkanya herself and mridangam in turns in that order turned out to be a showcase of vidwath. The most notable aspect was the perfect execution of their share of each passage with awe inspiring abandon.
